<https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/the-crown-estate> <http://ogp.me/ns#description> "The Crown Estate is an independent commercial business, created by an Act of Parliament, with a diverse portfolio of UK buildings, shoreline, seabed, forestry, agriculture and common land. The business generates valuable revenue for the government and over the last 10 years has contributed £4.1 billion to the Consolidated Fund. The Crown Estate works with HM Treasury ."@en <https://forgetmenot.local/extractor/rdfa> .
